{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"69ffb40d-046e-49a2-8b34-d45a1c6dbce3","content":"Good news — in .NET 10, `dotnet test` uses **Microsoft.Testing.Platform natively by default**. You **no longer need `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`** — it's redundant.\n\nHere's what to do:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01VrMHSqGBGv1mtSvoSu1qUb","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing redundant property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01Czyz172qxFE1PTPDKHsgcJ","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-0a963a19da3c49a1b8d8183e41ac9a3a/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>","new_str":"    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-0a963a19da3c49a1b8d8183e41ac9a3a/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"b3c3e402-110c-483a-9644-6d31a87abac7","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and wants to know about MTP support. Let me check what changed in .NET 10 regarding Microsoft.Testing.Platform and `dotnet test`.\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) by default — it's the new default test runner. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property is no longer needed because MTP integration is built-in.\n\nKey points:\n1. In .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively uses MTP — no need for `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport`.\n\n\n2. To make the test project an executable with the MSTest runner, I still need to set `EnableMSTestRunner`.\n3. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property becomes redundant on .NET 10 and can be removed.","outputTokens":514,"requestId":"A035:31275C:C9B7D9:EAD1EA:69FE8726"},"id":"f6be5c64-4d23-4214-8595-593532b88f8b","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:00:30.346Z","parentId":"024e880f-48d3-48ff-a560-c09fc0e9534f"}
